This paper describes a tool for multi-label categorization of documents using a thesaurus, which is a common task in natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of feature vectors, which is a common technique in deep learning, suggesting the sub-category cs.DL (Deep Learning).
